eed to stay within the h2 package. I plan to simplify things by replacing ValueSource strings with storage modes like \\\\\\\"file\\\\\\\" and \\\\\\\"memory\\\\\\\" for database URLs.\\\\n\\\\nI wonder if I really need to create directories since H2 handles that. I could use tempDir to manage paths. For Windows compatibility, I'll consider how backslashes might work with H2 JDBC URLs. I’ll also need to think about whether parallel tests could conflict and how using UUIDs for unique memory databases might help avoid that.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Considering UUID usage**\\\\n\\\\nI noticed that there's a UUID constant available, but it seems like there isn't a random one. I’ll need to think about how to generate a random UUID for my implementation when necessary. This could be important, especially for ensuring uniqueness in various scenarios. Having random UUIDs might help avoid conflicts, particularly in database testing. I wonder if I should incorporate `SecureRandom` for better randomness — that could be an interesting consideration!\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_H0uB4GqUujhvWsaDDwKs40fO|fc_0c23839a4307fdba0169f7294997dc819cad700fd484b4027d\", \"name\": \"edit\", \"arguments\": {\"path\": \"tests/src/com.h2database/h2/2.2.220/src/test/java/h2/H2Test.java\", \"edits\": [{\"oldText\": \"import org.h2.api.Interval;\\nimport org.junit.jupiter.params.ParameterizedTest;\\nimport org.junit.jupiter.params.provider.ValueSource;\\n\", \"newText\": \"import org.h2.api.Interval;\\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.io.TempDir;\\nimport org.junit.jupiter.params.ParameterizedTest;\\nimport org.junit.jupiter.params.provider.ValueSource;\\n\"}, {\"oldText\": \"import java.time.OffsetTime;\\nimport java.time.ZoneOffset;\\nimport java.util.UUID;\\n\", \"newText\": \"import java.time.OffsetTime;\\nimport java.time.ZoneOffset;\\nimport java.nio.file.Path;\\nimport java.util.UUID;\\n\"}, {\"oldText\": \"class H2Test {\\n    @ParameterizedTest\\n    @ValueSource(strings = {\\\"jdbc:h2:./data/test\\\", \\\"jdbc:h2:mem:db1;DB_CLOSE_DELAY=-1\\\"})\\n    void test(String url) throws Exception {\\n\", \"newText\": \"public class H2Test {\\n    @ParameterizedTest\\n    @ValueSource(strings = {\\\"file\\\", \\\"memory\\\"})\\n    void test(String storageMode, @TempDir Path tempDir) throws Exception {\\n        String url = databaseUrl(storageMode, tempDir);\\n\"}, {\"oldText\": \"    private static void withConnection(String url, ConnectionCallback callback) throws SQLException {\\n\", \"newText\": \"    private static String databaseUrl(String storageMode, Path tempDir) {\\n        if (\\\"file\\\".equals(storageMode)) {\\n            return \\\"jdbc:h2:\\\" + tempDir.resolve(\\\"test\\\").toAbsolutePath();\\n        }\\n        if (\\\"memory\\\".equals(storageMode)) {\\n            return \\\"jdbc:h2:mem:h2test\\\" + Integer.toUnsignedString(tempDir.hashCode()) + \\\";DB_CLOSE_DELAY=-1\\\";\\n        }\\n        throw new IllegalArgumentException(\\\"Unknown storage mode: \\\" + storageMode);\\n    }\\n\\n    private static void withConnection(String url, ConnectionCallback callback) throws SQLException {\\n\"}]}}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 568, \"output\": 1613, \"cacheRead\": 39936, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 42117, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\", \"timestamp\": 1777805623716, \"responseId\": \"resp_0c23839a4307fdba0169f729382a28819ca8ac22bd8b3576e6\"}}\nhuman-intervention-logs/com.h2database:h2:2.2.220/fix-java-run-fail/pi-generation-2026-05-03T10-54-31-401077Z.log:2209:[tool-exec] start id=call_H0uB4GqUujhvWsaDDwKs40fO|fc_0c23839a4307fdba0169f7294997dc819cad700fd484b4027d name=edit args={\"path\": \"tests/src/com.h2database/h2/2.2.220/src/test/java/h2/H2Test.java\", \"edits\": [{\"oldText\": \"import org.h2.api.Interval;\\ni